1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,534
A high-fit tender appears with one week left.

2
00:00:03,534 --> 00:00:07,510
The team must decide, reconstruct requirements,
coordinate the response,

3
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:10,161
and catch every amendment before submission.

4
00:00:10,161 --> 00:00:15,020
TenderGraph is an agentic tender operating system
for the complete workflow.

5
00:00:15,570 --> 00:00:19,808
Seven bounded agents cover the full bidding
lifecycle.

6
00:00:19,808 --> 00:00:24,046
A human qualification gate unlocks the bid plan.

7
00:00:24,046 --> 00:00:27,224
Two unresolved requirements still block compliance.

8
00:00:27,224 --> 00:00:30,403
No agent can release the bid.

9
00:00:30,403 --> 00:00:34,111
New evidence replans only the affected work.

10
00:00:34,661 --> 00:00:39,617
The operating layer is proven against a
hash-verified public evaluation.

11
00:00:39,617 --> 00:00:43,086
Every conclusion is bound to exact evidence.

12
00:00:43,086 --> 00:00:48,537
The inspector exposes source, page, quotation,
parser, authority, URL, and hash.

13
00:00:48,537 --> 00:00:52,502
A commission recommendation is not a signed
contract.

14
00:00:53,052 --> 00:00:58,029
The question runs through ChatGPT-authenticated
Codex without an API key.

15
00:00:58,029 --> 00:01:01,015
GPT-5.6 composes only from admitted claims.

16
00:01:01,015 --> 00:01:04,996
The trace retains the model and Session ID.

17
00:01:04,996 --> 00:01:09,475
Fifteen code-owned gates reject invention, evidence
swaps, scope contamination,

18
00:01:09,475 --> 00:01:11,466
leakage, and incomplete output.

19
00:01:12,016 --> 00:01:15,855
A new official PDF becomes hashed, addressable
evidence.

20
00:01:15,855 --> 00:01:18,734
It does not automatically become authority.

21
00:01:18,734 --> 00:01:22,573
Codex compares the update with every active
conclusion.

22
00:01:22,573 --> 00:01:28,332
Six gates validate scope, evidence, complete impact,
action semantics, and shadow authority.

23
00:01:28,332 --> 00:01:30,731
Nothing changes before human review.

24
00:01:31,281 --> 00:01:34,974
A corrective resolution is the harder test.

25
00:01:34,974 --> 00:01:38,666
The original winner and loss explanation change.

26
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:41,304
The award rule remains valid.

27
00:01:41,304 --> 00:01:46,579
The result matches the versioned reference and
cannot promote itself.

28
00:01:47,129 --> 00:01:51,300
The enforcement is measured: 49 tests and 23 golden
scenarios.

29
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:55,471
It includes 6 lifecycle, 15 composition, and 6
impact gates.

30
00:01:55,471 --> 00:01:58,808
The harness admitted 0 of 8 injected faults.

31
00:01:58,808 --> 00:02:02,145
This capture retains three real Codex Session IDs.

32
00:02:02,695 --> 00:02:07,619
Codex accelerated architecture, implementation,
testing, and production diagnosis.

33
00:02:07,619 --> 00:02:13,773
TenderGraph gives companies an agentic bidding team
with governed memory.

34
00:02:13,773 --> 00:02:19,312
Agents can discover, qualify, prepare, check,
monitor, and learn.

35
00:02:19,312 --> 00:02:23,620
GPT-5.6 can reason. Humans remain the authority.
